Rating: 3
This chowder made a satisfying meal with a few minor variations. I added one medium finely diced white potato and let it cook with the white parts of the green onion in the clam juice before adding the corn and milk. I also used dried ginger instead of fresh and only a teaspoon of lemon juice. I pureed only half of the pot leaving a few chunks. The chowder was served with a leafy green salad for dinner. The chowder was good enough to add to the rotation.

