Rating: 4
Although it's always a little irritating to read reviews that deviate from the recipe, particularly when it leads to a negative review, I had to make a change or two: jarred ground ginger paste (grocery store had no roots) and I used whole milk as I had it on hand. Also, I used an immersion blender. That said, this chowder got raves and was a true crowd pleaser on a winter night, and one recipe I will make this summer using fresh corn and serving cold. It was a perfect introduction to the crabcakes and popovers that followed. I doubled the recipe and it yielded 7 cups. Easy, elegant, great taste, texture, and presentation. A keeper.

